<tool id="gmlq_rest_login" name="GMLQ Login" version="0.1.0">
  <description>Login in the GMQL platform</description>
  <command interpreter="python">gmql_rest_auth.py $output -cmd=login -login_type=$authType.log_type
	  </command>
  <inputs>
	<conditional name="authType">
		<param name="log_type" type="select" label="Log as guest or registered?" >
			<option value="guest">Guest</option>
			<option value="registered">Registered User</option>			
		</param>
		<!-- For now, unused -->
 		<when value="registered">
			<param name="user" type="text" label="Username" />
			<param name="password" type="text" label="Password" />
		</when>
	</conditional>
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="json" name="output" label="GMQL ${authType.log_type} user" />
  </outputs>
  <help>
  **What it does**
  
  It allows to login into the GMQL platform. Every other operation request the user to be logged. 
  
  At the moment the only way is as a guest.
  
  </help>	
	
</tool>

